 <div class="title" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Results and discussion</div>
 <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Three independent series of luminescence spectroscopic experiments were performed. TRLFS experiments were run at 25 °C, making them comparable to literature (see 
  <a ref-type="table" rid="tab1" href="#tab1">Table 1</a>). For two additional series (TRLFS and CW spectroscopy) a temperature of 1 °C was chosen where the quantum yield of the uranyl(
  <span class="sc">vi</span>) aquo ion is 3.8 times higher compared to 20 °C (see 
  <a ref-type="fig" rid="fig2" href="#fig2">Fig. 2</a>).
 </p>
